This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with lane detection in driving scenes using deep neural networks. It may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the proposed method is relevant to autonomous vehicles and advanced driver assistance systems. Additionally, the paper involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for feature learning and prediction, which falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as it mentions the handling of difficult situations, which could include security threats.
